<br>
1. Break Mez<br>
2. Aggro Mobs by proxity.<br>
<br>
If you saw either of these, then there was a bug.<br>
<br>
Also, just something to temper what you saw: Just because you say a &quot;has broken mezz&quot; message doesn't mecessarily mean that the person named actually broke mezz. You can get that message also if you are beating on a mob that's had certain stuns cast on it (not necessarily for the purpose of mezzing).<br>
<br>
I freaked when I had that message show up on me twice in a row the last time I was in Chardok on Royals, but I was later reassured that I just happened to be the lucky winner of the &quot;who struck next&quot; contest after one of the chanters stunned the mob to interrupt their casting.<br>
<br>
Oh, and on the recovery without summoning? They probably had a cleric camped out either before the wipeout pull or perhaps successfully camped during the battle in question. If the room was clear of any mobs that are usually there, then the wipe out mobs would leave the room empty allowing the cleric to log back in. Also, I've been on more than one raid were we wiped other than a FD necro. The FD necro did a quick necro rez of a epic cleric (in some cases, they had to do a quick log and then log back in to clear aggro), and a full recovery was complete in as little about 5 minutes (longer in some cases of this). One of the reasons that Necros rule (though I wouldn't necessarily call them &quot;King&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub135.ezboard.com/bexodusfellowshipforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mnim>Mnim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(4/14/03 8:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1266.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   melee</span><hr size=1> I just want to clarify. My sole reason for posting this was for melees. Really, lol. <br>
